  </input></program></listing>
  <p>The code for splicing out shown below (see <xref ref="trees_lst-splice-out"/>), and it is a method of the <c>TreeNode</c> class. This code makes use
            of the same properties of binary search trees that cause an inorder
            traversal to print out the nodes in the tree from smallest to largest.</p>

  <listing xml:id="trees_lst-splice-out">
  <caption>Splicing a Successor into the Correct Location</caption>
  <program language="java"><input>
    void spliceOut() {
        if (this.isLeaf()) {
            if (this.isLeftChild()) {
                this.parent.leftChild = null;
            } else {
                this.parent.rightChild = null;
            }
        } else if (this.hasAnyChild()) {
            if (this.leftChild != null) {
                if (this.isLeftChild()) {
                    this.parent.leftChild = this.leftChild;
                } else {
                    this.parent.rightChild = this.leftChild;
                }
                this.leftChild.parent = this.parent;
            } else {
                if (this.isLeftChild()) {
                    this.parent.leftChild = this.rightChild;
                } else {
                    this.parent.rightChild = this.rightChild;
                }
                this.rightChild.parent = this.parent;
            }
        }
    }
